description: "A membrane-bounded organelle, specialized for the storage and secretion of various substances (surfactant phospholipids, glycoproteins and acid phosphates) which are arranged in the form of tightly packed, concentric, membrane sheets or lamellae. Has some similar properties to, but is distinct from, a lysosome." [GOC:cjm, GOC:jl, PMID:12243725, Wikipedia:Lamellar_granule]
name: lamellar body

description: "A type of endosome in which regions of the limiting endosomal membrane invaginate to form internal vesicles; membrane proteins that enter the internal vesicles are sequestered from the cytoplasm." [PMID:11566881, PMID:16533950]
name: multivesicular body

description: "A specialized secretory organelle found in type II pneumocytes and involved in the synthesis, secretion, and reutilization of pulmonary surfactant." [GOC:cjm, Wikipedia:Lamellar_granule]
name: alveolar lamellar body

description: "The volume enclosed by the outermost membrane of a multivesicular body." [GOC:pde, PMID:21183070]
name: multivesicular body lumen

description: "Any small, fluid-filled, spherical organelle enclosed by membrane." [GOC:mah, GOC:pz, GOC:vesicles]
name: vesicle

description: "The volume enclosed by the membrane of a late endosome." [GOC:mah]
name: late endosome lumen

description: "The space external to the outermost structure of a cell. For cells without external protective or external encapsulating structures this refers to space outside of the plasma membrane. This term covers the host cell environment outside an intracellular parasite." [GOC:go_curators]
name: extracellular region

description: "A clathrin-coated, membrane-bounded intracellular vesicle formed by invagination of the plasma membrane around an extracellular substance." [GOC:go_curators]
name: clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle

description: "A small subcellular vesicle, surrounded by a membrane, that is formed from the Golgi apparatus and contains a highly concentrated protein destined for secretion. Secretory granules move towards the periphery of the cell and upon stimulation, their membranes fuse with the cell membrane, and their protein load is exteriorized. Processing of the contained protein may take place in secretory granules." [GOC:mah, ISBN:0198506732]
name: secretory granule

description: "A prelysosomal endocytic organelle differentiated from early endosomes by lower lumenal pH and different protein composition. Late endosomes are more spherical than early endosomes and are mostly juxtanuclear, being concentrated near the microtubule organizing center." [NIF_Subcellular:nlx_subcell_20090702, PMID:11964142, PMID:2557062]
name: late endosome

description: "That part of a multicellular organism outside the cells proper, usually taken to be outside the plasma membranes, and occupied by fluid." [ISBN:0198547684]
name: extracellular space

description: "A cytoplasmic, membrane bound vesicle that is capable of fusing to the plasma membrane to release its contents into the extracellular space." [GOC:dos]
name: secretory vesicle
